                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1019">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/9–744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 16, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2220. Reference your 3364 of September 7. The extent to which the Department
                    wishes to insist on the Soviet Government’s agreement to the Department’s <hi
                        rend="italic">Aide-Mémoire</hi> of July 6 is still under consideration. The
                    Department suggests, therefore, that if you feel it desirable, you inquire of
                    the Soviet Government, without discussing the contents of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Aide-Mémoire</hi>, when a reply may be expected.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
